Sri Lanka Reaches 166-2, Trails Australia by 150 in Cricket Test

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-09-17T15:23:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/sri-lanka-reaches-166-2-trails-australia-by-150-in-cricket-test.html
Kumar Sangakkara’s unbeaten 61
helped Sri Lanka reach 166-2 on day two of the third cricket
Test against  Australia  in Colombo.  Tharanga Paranavitana scored 46 runs and Mahela Jayawardene
is 31 not out in Sri Lanka’s response to Australia’s first
innings 316.  Michael Hussey  scored 118, his second century of
the series, for the visitors.  Australia won the opener of the three-game series by 125
runs, while the second Test was drawn. Australia will move above
Sri Lanka to fourth in the International Cricket Council Test
rankings by winning the series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  